  "titles": "Fulgrim Transfigured The Phoenician Deified, Avatar of Perfection",
  "lore": "Fulgrim’s desire for perfection in all things left his mind open to doubt, the seeds of which were nurtured by the malevolent spirit that inhabited the Blade of the Laer and his own hubris. Since his apotheosis to daemonhood in the ancient xenos citadel deep beneath the crone world of Lydris, Fulgrim has been able to shift his appearance between a more humanoid guise and a monstrous form gifted by his new patron. With a serpentine lower half, vast wings and a pair of additional arms, Fulgrim’s new body elevated an already deadly warrior to even greater heights, closer to the perfection he so craved.",
